        <p>We fix the immediate failure, but we also tell you what maintenance prevents the next one: consistent rinse-aid in every dishwasher cycle, a quarterly filter clean, and an inline water filter on your refrigerator supply line. These are cheap preventive measures that extend appliance lifespan significantly in Simi Valley.</p>

        <h3>2. Dryer vents and fire risk in Santa Ana conditions</h3>
        <p>Simi Valley's location — surrounded by hills and exposed to Santa Ana wind patterns — creates elevated fire risk conditions during late summer and fall. A dryer vent clogged with lint is a fire hazard under normal conditions. In Simi Valley during a Santa Ana event, it's a more serious one.</p>
        <p>We inspect dryer vents on every dryer repair call in Simi Valley. If the thermal fuse is failing repeatedly, we look at the vent before we replace anything. A restricted vent will keep blowing fuses indefinitely — it's not the fuse's fault. We clear the vent, replace the failed components, and document the vent condition in our service report.</p>
